甲.definition: first of the ten Heavenly Stems 十天干[shi2 tian1 gan1]; (used for an unspecified person or thing); first (in a list, as a party to a contract etc); letter "A" or roman "I" in list "A, B, C", or "I, II, III" etc; armor plating; shell or carapace; (of the fingers or toes) nail; bladed leather or metal armor (old); ranking system used in the Imperial examinations (old); civil administration unit in the baojia 保甲[bao3 jia3] system (old); ancient Chinese compass point: 75°

甲之蜜糖，乙之砒霜.pinyin: jia3 zhi1 mi4 tang2 , yi3 zhi1 pi1 shuang1
甲之蜜糖，乙之砒霜.definition: one man's meat is another man's poison (idiom)

甲乙.definition: first two of the ten Heavenly Stems 十天干[shi2 tian1 gan1]

甲亢.definition: hyperthyroidism; abbr. for 甲狀腺功能亢進|甲状腺功能亢进[jia3 zhuang4 xian4 gong1 neng2 kang4 jin4]

甲午.definition: thirty-first year A7 of the 60 year cycle, e.g. 1954 or 2014

甲基安非他命.pinyin: jia3 ji1 an1 fei1 ta1 ming4

甲子.definition: first year of the sixty-year cycle (where each year is numbered with one of the 10 heavenly stems 天干[tian1 gan1] and one of the 12 earthly branches 地支[di4 zhi1]); the sixty-year cycle

甲寅.definition: 51st year A3 of the 60 year cycle, e.g. 1974 or 2034

甲戌.definition: eleventh year A11 of the 60 year cycle, e.g. 1994 or 2054

甲方.definition: party A (in a contract) (cf. 乙方[yi3fang1], party B)

甲殼.definition: carapace; crust; outer shell; also pr. [jia3 ke2]

甲殼蟲類.definition: insects of the order Coleoptera (i.e. beetles)

甲流.definition: type A influenza; abbr. for 甲型H1N1流感; refers to H1N1 influenza of 2009

甲狀腺功能亢進.pinyin: jia3 zhuang4 xian4 gong1 neng2 kang4 jin4
甲狀腺功能亢進.definition: hyperthyroidism; abbr. to 甲亢[jia3 kang4]

甲狀腺素.definition: thyroid hormone; thyroxine (used to treat underactive thyroid)

甲申.definition: 21st year A9 of the 60 year cycle, e.g. 2004 or 2064

甲申政變.definition: unsuccessful and bloody Korean palace coup in 1884 by Westernisers against conservatives, crushed by Qing troops

甲第.definition: residence of a noble; top candidate in the imperial examinations

甲辰.definition: 41st year A5 of the 60 year cycle, e.g. 1964 or 2024

甲酸.definition: formylic acid (HCOOH); formic acid; methanoic acid

甲醇.definition: methyl alcohol; methanol CH3OH; wood alcohol; wood spirit

甲骨.definition: tortoise shells and animal bones used for divination in the Shang Dynasty (c. 16th to 11th century BC); oracle bones

甲骨文.definition: oracle script; oracle bone inscriptions (an early form of Chinese script)

甲骨文字.definition: oracle script; oracle bone character (an early form of Chinese script)
